### Refactor 1 — extract isFeedRowClickBlocked predicate

Files changed:
- feedRowPredicates.ts: +16 lines (new export isFeedRowClickBlocked)
- feedReducer.ts: -4 lines (import + replace inline guard)
- FeedRow.svelte: -2 lines (replace inline rowDisabled ternary)

Motivation: REQ-FEED-005/006 guard logic was duplicated identically in
feedReducer.ts (FeedRowClicked branch) and FeedRow.svelte ($derived rowDisabled).
Extracting to feedRowPredicates.ts eliminates the duplication and gives the
predicate a VCSDD-traceable name (maps to PROP-FEED-005..007 guard semantics).
Pure core: no side effects introduced.

Post-refactor: bun 1463 pass / vitest 174 pass

### Refactor 2 — document filterApplied prop intent in FeedList.svelte

Files changed:
- FeedList.svelte: type alias FeedListViewState, rename _filterApplied → filterApplied

Motivation: `FeedViewState & { filterApplied?: boolean }` was an undocumented
inline intersection on the Props type. Named the intersection type FeedListViewState
to make intent explicit. Renamed the internal state variable from _filterApplied
(underscore convention suggests private/hack) to filterApplied (clean name).
Full prop separation was attempted but reverted because the existing test passes
filterApplied via the viewState spread — test contract preserved as-is.

Post-refactor: bun 1463 pass / vitest 174 pass

### Refactor 3 — extract nowIso() clock helper

Files changed:
- clockHelpers.ts: +19 lines (new effectful shell file, nowIso() function)
- FeedRow.svelte: -3 lines (nowIso() replaces 3× new Date().toISOString())
- DeleteConfirmModal.svelte: -3 lines (nowIso() replaces 2× new Date().toISOString())
- DeletionFailureBanner.svelte: -2 lines (nowIso() replaces 1× new Date().toISOString())

Motivation: new Date().toISOString() was scattered across 3 shell components
(6 call sites total). Centralising into nowIso() in clockHelpers.ts gives a
single testable entry point and aligns with the editor feature's injected clock
pattern. clockHelpers.ts is NOT in PURE_MODULES — purity audit is unaffected.
PROP-FEED-031 confirmed clean via bun test purityAudit.test.ts.

Post-refactor: bun 1463 pass / vitest 174 pass

